# pip-tools bootstrap — the toolchain that *regenerates the other two
# lockfiles* (requirements-dev.txt, requirements-build.txt) inside the
# two lockfile-drift guard jobs in ci.yml. Hash-pinned via
# `requirements-pip-tools.txt` so the guards that enforce supply-chain
# integrity are themselves installed with verified integrity, instead of
# the bare `pip install pip-tools==7.5.3` that Scorecard flags as
# `pipCommand not pinned by hash` (Pinned-Dependencies; alerts #10/#11,
# closes #224).
#
# Regenerate (Python 3.12, pip-tools 7.5.3 — same toolchain as the other
# two lockfiles; see CLAUDE.md):
#   pip-compile --generate-hashes --no-strip-extras --allow-unsafe -o requirements-pip-tools.txt requirements-pip-tools.in
#
# `--allow-unsafe` is REQUIRED: pip-tools depends on setuptools + wheel,
# which pip-tools classifies as "unsafe to pin" and comments out by
# default — but `pip install --require-hashes` is all-or-nothing, so an
# un-pinned transitive dep would make the install fail. `--no-strip-extras`
# mirrors the other two lockfiles (pip-tools 8.0 default-flip defense).
#
# Pinned to the exact version mandated by CLAUDE.md for lockfile
# regeneration; bump deliberately, in lockstep with the version used by
# the two guard jobs and the regeneration commands in CLAUDE.md.
pip-tools==7.5.3
